Problem:
Run wireshark as non-root user, cannot see/capture eth0.

Solution:
sudo dpkg-reconfigure wireshark-common
# chose yes to enable non-root user capture
sudo adduser <username> wireshark
# reboot

Related doc:
/usr/share/doc/wireshark-common/README.Debian

System and software info:
Ubuntu 14.04 x86_64
wireshark 1.10.6 (v1.10.6 from master-1.10)
